# UI Components and React Aria Conventions

## Design system first

- Use `@laitram-l-l-c/intralox-ui-components` for buttons, inputs, selects, popovers, and modals when available.
- Wrap DS primitives in `src/components/ui/` — do not re-implement RAC primitives that the DS already exports.
- Promote reusable patterns to the DS with Chromatic stories when multiple apps need them.

## When to use `react-aria-components` directly

Use RAC in the app only when the DS does not expose the primitive:

- `RangeCalendar` / `DateField` / `DateSegment` composition
- Accessible data tables (`Table`, `Row`, `Column`, `Cell`)
- Full overlay shells not covered by DS exports (see `AppDialogShell`)

Do not import `@react-aria/*` hooks in customer-portal — use `react-aria-components` or the DS.

## Contribution conventions (Chromatic)

Authoritative docs (internal):

https://main--656e2fad67b38b22e605fc23.chromatic.com/?path=/docs/contribution-component-conventions--docs

Until mirrored in-repo, follow these RAC patterns:

### Dialogs and overlays

```tsx
<ModalOverlay isOpen={isOpen} onOpenChange={...} isDismissable>
  <Modal>
    <Dialog>
      {({ close }) => (
        <>
          <Heading slot="title">Title</Heading>
          {/* content */}
        </>
      )}
    </Dialog>
  </Modal>
</ModalOverlay>
```

- Use controlled `isOpen` / `onOpenChange` — **do not** `return null` when closed (breaks enter/exit and focus).
- Prefer `AppDialogShell` in `src/components/shared/app-dialog-shell/` for app modals.

### Buttons and press

- RAC `Button`: use `onPress`, not `onClick`.
- DS `Button` wrappers: forward `onPress` via DS props.

### Forms (direct RAC only)

- Compose `TextField` → `Label` + `Input` + `FieldError` when not using DS `Input`.

### Tables

- Set `aria-label` on `Table`.
- Wire `selectedKeys` / `onSelectionChange` to RAC selection — avoid parallel checkbox state.
- Use stable row `id` values for selection.

### Styling RAC components

- Prefer `className` render props: `({ isPressed, isFocusVisible }) => cn(...)`.
- Use design-system Tailwind tokens, not `gray-*` or arbitrary hex.

### Dates

- Use `@internationalized/date` with `I18nProvider` for calendars.

## File placement

| Location | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `src/components/ui/` | Thin DS wrappers (portal variants) |
| `src/components/shared/` | App-wide shells (modal, panel, toast) |
| `src/components/core/*/` | Feature-specific UI |

